It's a small tool can be used to take away a number of memory from your android device.
The tool was designed to observe what happens when running cases on a low-end devices with a small mount of RAM.
The oom_adj value is automatically set to prevent lowmemkiller killing the process when it running.

Usage:
1.Download the ndk package and set the ndk enviroment variable.
2.Run ndk-build in jni directory.
3.Choose the binary file to run in your device according to you platform.

